Event Stream
Event Source
Event Processor
Event Sink


Event Sources produce events to Event Stream

Event Processor and Event Sinks consumes them


Event Stream
-------------


In Appache Kafka, Event Streams are called topics


Streaming technologies support Kafka-based Event Streams as a core abstraction. For example

|> The Kafka Streams DSL API provides abstractions for Event Streams, notably the KStream interface for unbounded data streams and KTable interface
   for changelog data on keyed records(e.g KTable of product updates keyed on product ID)






